votes.evidence:
I independently re-traced the full chain in frontend/src/pages/WorkspaceDetailPage/WorkspaceDetailPage.tsx.

State + effect (verified line numbers): line 940 `const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null)`; the fetch effect (lines 963-977):
```
useEffect(() => {
  if (!workspaceId) return
  async function fetchWorkspace() {
    setLoading(true)                 // 966
    try {
      const data = await workspaceApi.getDetail(workspaceId!)
      setWorkspace(data)             // 969  -- NO setError(null) here or above
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err instanceof ApiError ? err.message : "Failed to load workspace")  // 971
    } finally {
      setLoading(false)              // 973
    }
  }
  void fetchWorkspace()
}, [workspaceId])
```
`grep setError` over the file confirms the page-level component calls setError ONLY at line 971 (the catch). There is no `setError(null)` in the success path or at effect start. The render gate is line 994: `if (error || !workspace) return <div ...>{error ?? "Workspace not found"}</div>`. So once `error` is set by a failed load, a later successful load sets `workspace` and clears `loading`, but `error` stays truthy → the error screen renders for a valid workspace.

Reachability is real and live:
- Routing (src/router.tsx lines 40 and 44) maps BOTH `workspaces/:workspaceId` and `workspaces/:slug/:workspaceId` to the SAME `<WorkspaceDetailPage />` element (same in src/pages/EmbedPage.tsx lines 44/46). No `key` prop on either route, so a param-only navigation does NOT remount the component — `error` state survives.
- WorkspaceSwitcher (src/components/WorkspaceSwitcher/WorkspaceSwitcher.tsx) drives in-place navigation: `select()` (lines 260-274) navigates to `workspacePath(ws)` when already on a `/workspaces/...` detail path, and `manage()` (lines 276-279) always navigates to another workspace's detail page. The top-bar gear (lines 371-384, `data-testid="topbar-workspace-settings"`) also calls `navigate(workspacePath(activeWorkspace))`. These are live UI elements wired to the live router.

Confirming contrast that proves intent/bug: the sibling members fetch in the same file (different component, line 35) DOES reset `setError(null)` at line 52 before fetching — the page-level effect omits this exact line.

Trigger sequence reproduced by trace: (1) mount on a dead/stale workspace link → getDetail throws → setError → error screen; (2) without remount, click the switcher/gear to a valid workspace → effect refires (workspaceId dep), setLoading(true), success → setWorkspace(data), setLoading(false), but error still set → line 994 still returns the error screen until a full remount/hard refresh.
